    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Agent
    Agent is the interface for any node in the directed acyclic computational graph.
    BinOpAgent
    BinOpAgent represents a binary-operation node in the computational graph.
    Config
    Config is an interface for any configuration source that can supply a mapping of initial numeric nodes and a mapping of expressions for building a computational graph.
    ConfLoader
    ConfLoader servlet handles HTTP POST requests to "/upload".
    GenericConfig
    GenericConfig reads and stores a user‐provided configuration file that defines named nodes either as numeric values or as expressions.
    Graph
    Graph builds and holds all Agent nodes for the computational DAG based on a GenericConfig.
    HtmlGraphWriter
    HtmlGraphWriter generates a full HTML page (including JavaScript and a canvas element) that visualizes the computational graph defined by a GenericConfig.
    HtmlLoader
    Serves static HTML files from a directory.
    HTTPServer
    HTTPServer defines the minimal interface for an HTTP server implementation.
    IncAgent
    IncAgent represents a unary increment node that adds 1.0 to the computed value of a predecessor Agent.
    Main
     
    MathExampleConfig
    MathExampleConfig provides a hardcoded demonstration configuration for testing.
    Message
    Message encapsulates a text string that can be published to a Topic.
    MyHTTPServer
    MyHTTPServer implements a simple reusable HTTP server library.
    Node
    Node is a simple data holder representing a single line of configuration, containing the node’s name and its right‐hand side string (either a numeric value or an expression).
    ParallelAgent
    ParallelAgent wraps two Agents and computes both in (conceptual) parallel, returning the sum of their computed values.
    PlusAgent
    PlusAgent represents a node that adds a constant offset to the computed value of its single predecessor Agent.
    RequestParser
    RequestParser provides utility to parse a raw HTTP request from a BufferedReader and produce a RequestInfo object containing method, URI, headers, and query parameters.
    RequestParser.RequestInfo
    Parses an HTTP request line and headers from the provided BufferedReader.
    Servlet
    Servlet is the interface that all request-handling classes must implement.
    Topic
    Topic represents a named channel to which Messages can be published.
    TopicDisplayer
    TopicDisplayer servlet handles HTTP GET requests to "/publish".
    TopicManagerSingleton
    TopicManagerSingleton is a thread-safe singleton that manages all Topics in the system.
    TopicManagerSingleton.TopicManager
    TopicManager manages all Topics in the system.
